devdoc.details: Smart contract for managing a benefactor's dead man's switch with assigned beneficiaries.

addBeneficiary(address,string[]).details: Adds a new beneficiary to the list. Only callable by the benefactor.

params._beneficiary: The address of the new beneficiary.
params._ipfsCIDs: An array of IPFS CIDs associated with the new beneficiary.

addIpfsCID(address,string).details: Adds an IPFS CID to the specified beneficiary. Only callable by the benefactor.

checkAliveStatus().details: Checks the alive status of the benefactor.

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the benefactor is alive.

constructor.details: Constructor to initialize the BenefactorsDeadManSwitch contract.

enableSwitch().details: Enables the dead man's switch. Only callable by beneficiaries.

returns._0: The remaining countdown time in seconds.

isBeneficiary(address).details: Checks if the given address is a beneficiary. Only benefactor

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the address is a beneficiary.

removeBeneficiary(address).details: Removes a beneficiary from the list. Only callable by the benefactor.

params._beneficiary: The address of the beneficiary to be removed.

removeIpfsCID(address,string).details: Removes an IPFS CID from the specified beneficiary. Only callable by benefactor.

respondToSwitch().details: Performs actions based on benefactor's activity when responding to an enabled switch. Only callable by the benefactor.
